Name: Momma B
ReviewText:
This hotel is in serious need of maintenance and remodel. We stayed here and had to change rooms because the first one was so horrible, but even the "upgradedâ€œ room was terrible! This was definitely far from the Disney standard that we expect especially with it still being Disney prices. There was mold in the showers, the tub did not drain, the lock in our first room and heater did not work. There was chipped paint, it was very dirty, over all disappointing. Not to mention these are incredibly small rooms with no fridge, coffee machines, or any accommodations. The design of the bathrooms was horrible. There was no way to keep everything from being completely soaked anytime someone would shower.
The most mortifying part was on our last day the staff walked into our room two separate times within 15 minutes of eachother while I was nursing my baby. No knocking, they just let themselves in. I could understand if it was past check out time but it was not! Absolutely horrific.
We were also incredibly frustrated with the meal plan. We purchased the full board plus meal plan which was supposed to include full course meals for lunch and dinner, breakfast, an alcoholic or fancy drink for each of us per day, and tea time for each of us each day. Over all we honestly were ripped off. If you do a meal plan, only do breakfast. We asked probably over 15 cast members where we could use our tea time at and nobody knew. The one place that we were told we could use it at refused to take it and said their card reader was down. So we paid for a bunch of I paid tea time. We also were incredibly upset to find out that one of the restaurants used two of our alcoholic drinks for coffees. So instead of getting two $10-$15 drinks we got two $3 coffees. Thankfully at another restaurant one of the cast members did. correct that for us, but it was still very upsetting.

Cheyenne is a mid tier resort, so it acts like one. I've stayed in all Disneyland Paris hotels and fell in love with the amazing atmosphere of this one. The Wild West theming is perfectly done and it feels like a western town. The rooms were very good as they were renovated not long ago (better than Sequoia Lodge's). The breakfast and food were really nice as well, it also has a Starbucks!
The one downside of this hotel is the way it's laid out, you can get a room that's pretty far away from the facilities. This makes it a bit far from the parks with a 15-20 minute walk, buses are free though. This isn't a problem for me, as it let me enjoy the hotel vistas even more.
Recommend it!

La plupart du temps, nous avons marchÃ© jusqu'au parc, choisissant de payer pour une section plus calme, nous avons Ã©tÃ© placÃ©s dans Doc Holiday, qui se trouvait au fond. AgrÃ©able et calme, Ã  l'exception de certains invitÃ©s au-delÃ  de minuit agissant comme des Ã©lÃ©phants en fuite, mais c'Ã©tait surtout agrÃ©able et paisible Ã  tout autre moment. Le bonus supplÃ©mentaire Ã©tant Ã  cette extrÃ©mitÃ© Ã©tait d'Ãªtre le plus proche des parcs, donc la marche ne prenait que moins de 10 minutes jusqu'Ã  Disney Village et dans les parcs.
Les draps n'ont jamais Ã©tÃ© changÃ©s pendant les 3 jours que nous avons passÃ©s lÃ -bas.
Le systÃ¨me de bagages express Disney Ã©tait pratique pour la matinÃ©e, tous envoyÃ©s Ã  la gare tout en profitant de la derniÃ¨re journÃ©e dans les parcs. Ensuite, collecte Ã  la gare assez facile.
Je n'ai pas pu m'empÃªcher de penser que tout le thÃ¨me occidental aurait pu Ãªtre meilleur, par exemple des personnes rÃ©elles habillÃ©es en cow-boys faisant des commentaires aux invitÃ©s. MÃªme un peu d'une fusillade maintenant n comme la faÃ§on dont les films occidentaux vont. Peut-Ãªtre trop Disney pour que quelqu'un se fasse tirer dessus mÃªme s'il fait semblant je suppose...
L'eau est trÃ¨s chÃ¨re Ã  3,30 EUR - pas de fruits dans le magasin, un bon conseil est d'apporter des collations / fruits, etc. Ã  St Pancras avant de partir pour la France.
Sur une note sÃ©parÃ©e, dans les parcs, il y a le problÃ¨me quotidien des resquilleurs. L'astuce qu'ils font est qu'une personne fait semblant d'Ãªtre au tÃ©lÃ©phone, regardant devant la file d'attente en prÃ©tendant que son ami les attend. Il n'y a pas d'ami, ils trouvent une position appropriÃ©e prÃ¨s de l'avant, pas trop prÃ¨s car le personnel Ã  l'entrÃ©e du manÃ¨ge les verra, puis leurs autres amis font exactement la mÃªme chose, s'ils ne sont pas dÃ©jÃ  avec eux. Cela s'est produit les 4 jours oÃ¹ nous Ã©tions dans les parcs, les autres clients de la file d'attente ont acceptÃ© et retenu le plus.
(Avis d'origine)
Aircon didn't work, just normal airflow but luckily the ceiling fan helped improve things. Queuing for breakfast can take time, unless after 10am which seemed to then have no ques. Most staff are very helpful, one young girl on the till was more interested in viewing photos on her phone and messaging her friends. This was under the nose of customers and her colleagues, not sure what the local custom is but when at work usually it doesn't mean you're act like being at home relaxing. As a result a mistake was made on my card which her more professional colleague happily resolved. Breakfast was acceptable, it was included on our magic passes, very expensive for what it is however.
Most days we walked to the park, opting to pay for a quieter section we were placed into Doc Holiday which was at the far end. Nice and quiet with exception of some guests beyond midnight acting like stampeding elephants but was mostly nice and peaceful all other times. Extra bonus being at this end was being closest to the parks, therefore walking only took less than 10mins to Disney Village and onto the parks.
Bed sheets were never changed in the 3 days we were there.
Disney express luggage system was handy for the morning, all sent to the train station whilst enjoying the last day in the parks. Then collecting at the station easy enough.
I couldn't help but feel the whole western theme could have been better, for example actual people dressed as cowboys making comments to guests. Even a bit of a shootout now n then like the way Western movies go. Maybe too Disney for someone to get shot even if pretend I guess....
Water is very expensive being 3.30 EUR - no fruit in the shop, good tip is to bring snacks/fruit etc at St Pancras before heading off to France.
On a seperate note, in the parks there is the daily issue of queue jumpers. The trick they do is one person pretends to be on their phone, looking up ahead of the queue pretending their friend is there waiting for them. There is no friend, they find a suitable position near the front, not too close as the staff at the ride entrance will see them, and then their other friends do the exact same thing, if they are not already with them. This happened on all 4 days we were at the parks, other guests in the queue agreed and held most back.

Enjoyable stay during a busy UK half term week. We arrived at 9am to pick up magic passes, which are your park tickets and hotel room key. We were text messaged at 2pm to tell us the room number. The room was relatively big and very clean. Two double beds were quite firm and only had one pillow per side. There was one UK plug socket, with all other sockets being French. The room did not had a fridge, iron or kettle. We did not need these so did not ask if they had them on request. The one complaint we had was the curtains did not really block out the sun. WiFi was great and easy to login to.
The hotel is about 15 min walk to Disney village and about 20 to the gates of Disneyland Park. There is a Starbucks and a couplemof other restaurants on site that we did not use.
There is a Woody or Jesse meet in the morning. They switch every half hour or so.
Overall great experience and hotel. We will definitely return.

During our stay at Disney the hotel was superb.
Our check in was simple and our room was ready hours before we expected, staff were always on hand to answer our questions especially as we were new to Disney
breakfast was always good with lively staff available at all times, our six year old would frequently dress as a Disney Princess and she would always get bows and curtsies from the staff
The food was great with a lovely wife selection of hot and cold.
The room was cleaned daily and we were provided fresh soaps and towels each day
The one major issue we experienced was the lack of a bath mat, sadly my wife slipped and hit her head on the counter next to the bath, this could have been a major qccidant but thankfully it wasn't, if there's one thing to improve here Disney it's supplying bath mats in the rooms!
The only other minor gripe we have is the location, the fifteen minute walk to the park is tougher for grandma and grandads to walk so was a bit of a chore bit if you are a younger family the location is great and the theming is just awesome
Overall a good hotel and we'll definitely be staying again!

L'enregistrement depuis la maison via l'application Disney est vivement recommandÃ©, cela rÃ©duit considÃ©rablement le temps d'attente pour l'enregistrement ! Sacs vÃ©rifiÃ©s par la sÃ©curitÃ© Ã  l'entrÃ©e la plupart du temps de la journÃ©e. Starbucks et boutique de souvenirs disponibles. Des boissons fraÃ®ches non alcoolisÃ©es, du vin, de la biÃ¨re, des cartons de lait, etc. sont Ã©galement disponibles dans la boutique de souvenirs.
Les chambres sont rÃ©parties dans plusieurs bÃ¢timents de la propriÃ©tÃ©. Votre pass magique est votre billet d'entrÃ©e aux parcs et aussi la clÃ© de votre chambre.
Chaque bÃ¢timent dispose Ã©galement d'un distributeur de boissons avec cafÃ©, cappuccino et chocolat chaud. Chaque passe magique contient un crÃ©dit pour obtenir des boissons de la machine tous les jours.
Vous pouvez demander une bouilloire pour la chambre par tÃ©lÃ©phone dans votre chambre Ã  la rÃ©ception.
La chambre est soignÃ©e avec TV, canapÃ©-lit, lit double avec une couette double. Le lit est assez Ã©troit (1,40 m). Des oreillers en quantitÃ© suffisante sont disponibles. Vous pouvez Ã©galement trouver un coffre-fort dans la chambre.
La salle de bain est spacieuse avec WC, grand lavabo et baignoire dans laquelle on peut se doucher.
Il y a une grande bouteille de savon dans le support et sur l'Ã©vier, vous trouverez un savon, un mini shampoing et un mini conditionneur sur le thÃ¨me de Toy Story.
Toujours en cette pÃ©riode de Covid, le lit a Ã©tÃ© fait et les serviettes remplacÃ©es.
Le petit dÃ©jeuner est bon, pas de buffet maintenant, mais Ã  la carte Ã  volontÃ©.
Pour nous, le plateau anglais et amÃ©ricain n'Ã©tait pas si appÃ©tissant. Bacon trÃ¨s salÃ© et Å“ufs brouillÃ©s humides. Les crÃªpes et les assiettes avec des produits coupÃ©s Ã©taient bonnes. Beaucoup de sandwichs, croissants et sandwichs au chocolat, tous mini. Au petit-dÃ©jeuner, vous pourrez choisir entre du jus d'eau, du jus de pomme, du cafÃ©, du thÃ© et du lait au chocolat aqueux.
DÃ®ner 1x utilisÃ©, pas de buffet maintenant mais illimitÃ© Ã  la carte. 1 boisson (sans alcool) pp incluse dans le prix. Nous nous sommes sentis un peu pressÃ©s, aprÃ¨s avoir enregistrÃ© votre plat arrive dans la minute et votre assiette est (presque) vide puis ils sont Ã  nouveau devant vous pour tout ramasser. Ne vous attendez pas Ã  de la haute qualitÃ©, mais Ã  de la viande sÃ¨che et des frites faibles
Dessert Le crumble aux pommes avec glace Ã  la vanille est fortement recommandÃ©.
Personnel amical et serviable, tout le monde ne parle pas anglais, mais ils ont quelqu'un qui parle anglais.
(Avis d'origine)
Een leuk thema hotel, qua prijs een van de goedkoopste in de Disney stal.
Inchecken vanuit thuis via de Disney app is zeker aan te raden, dit verkort de wachttijd van inchecken aanzienlijk! Bij binnenkomst op de meeste momenten van de dag tassen controle door de beveiliging. Starbucks en souvenir winkeltje aanwezig. In het souvenir winkeltje zijn ook koude frisdranken, wijn, bier, pakjes melk e.d verkrijgbaar.
De kamers zijn verdeeld over verschillende gebouwen over het terrein. Je magic pass is je entree kaart voor de parken en ook de sleutel voor je kamer.
In ieder gebouw staat ook een drankautomaat met koffie, cappuccino, warme chocolademelk. Op iedere magic pass zit een tegoed om dagelijks drankjes uit de automaat te halen.
Je kunt via de telefoon op je kamer bij de receptie een waterkoker vragen voor op de kamer.
Kamer is netjes met tv, bedbank, 2 persoonsbed met een 2 persoonsdekbed. Bed is vrij smal (1.40m). Er zijn voldoende kussens aanwezig. Ook een kluis kun je vinden op de kamer.
De badkamer is ruim met toilet, grote wastafel en bad waarin je kunt douchen.
Er hangt een grote fles zeep in houder en op de wastafel vind je een zeepje, mini shampoo en mini conditior in Toy Story thema.
Ook in deze Covid tijd werd het bed opgemaakt en de handdoeken vervangen.
Het ontbijt is prima, niet in buffet vorm nu, maar a la carte onbeperkt.
Voor ons was de Engelse en Amerikaanse platter niet zo smakelijk. Erg zoute bacon en natte roerei. De pannekoekjes en bordjes met snijwaren smaakten goed. Voldoende broodjes, croissants en chocolade broodjes, allemaal mini. Bij het ontbijt keuze uit water jus, appelsap, koffie, thee en waterige chocolademelk.
Het diner 1x gebruikt, ook nu geen buffet maar a la carte onbeperkt. 1 drankje (geen alcohol) pp inbegrepen in de prijs. Voelden ons wel wat opgejaagd, na opnemen komt binnen 1 minuut je gerecht en is je bord (bijna) leeg dan staan ze meteen weer voor je neus om alles af te halen. Verwacht geen hoge kwaliteit, maar droog vlees en slappe friet ğŸ™ˆ
Toetje Apple crumble met vanilleijs is wÃ©l een aanrader.
Wel vriendelijk en behulpzaam personeel, niet iedereen spreekt Engels, maar ze halen dan iemand die wel Engels spreekt.

C'est Ã  environ 15 minutes Ã  pied des parcs. Beaucoup d'espace pour que les enfants puissent courir et jouer Ã  l'extÃ©rieur. Il y avait un sÃ¨che-cheveux et un coffre-fort dans la chambre. Mais pas de bouilloire, de thÃ© ou de cafÃ© ou de micro-ondes. Une tÃ©lÃ©vision de taille correcte, mais pas grand chose Ã  regarder (pas que tout le monde va regarder beaucoup la tÃ©lÃ©vision dans un complexe Disney!). Le WiFi dans la chambre Ã©tait correct, sauf une nuit, il n'y avait pas de connexion Internet. J'avais en fait lu qu'il n'y avait que le WiFi dans le hall et le restaurant de l'hÃ´tel, donc l'avoir dans la chambre Ã©tait une surprise inattendue. TrÃ¨s propre, trÃ¨s sÃ»r avec une excellente sÃ©curitÃ©. Tous les employÃ©s parlaient anglais et franÃ§ais, et certains parlaient Ã©galement d'autres langues.
Les inconvÃ©nients de l'endroit. Il a fallu TOUJOURS pour nous enregistrer. Nous avons fait la queue pendant environ une demi-heure, et c'Ã©tait un jour lent. Ils prenaient prÃ¨s de 10 minutes par famille et il y avait beaucoup de va-et-vient des employÃ©s. Ils ne semblaient pas disposer des informations dont ils avaient besoin ni de l'autoritÃ© pour faire diverses choses. Il n'y a pas d'eau chaude, juste tiÃ¨de. Ce qui rendait les douches dÃ©sagrÃ©ables et les bains juste froids. J'ai appelÃ© la maintenance, et un gars vraiment agrÃ©able est sorti et a rÃ©ussi Ã  ajuster quelque chose qui a rÃ©chauffÃ© l'eau Ã  une tempÃ©rature assez confortable. Les baignoires sont SUPER SLIPPERY (oui, toutes les baignoires sont glissantes, mais c'Ã©tait glissant de glace!), MÃ©fiez-vous de cela! J'ai pris un bain et j'ai Ã©tÃ© incapable de me relever parce que mes pieds glissaient sous moi. Il y avait une poignÃ©e d'un cÃ´tÃ©, mais je ne pouvais mÃªme pas me tenir debout Ã  deux mains. J'ai rÃ©ussi Ã  attraper la serviette de sol et Ã  la mettre dans la baignoire, et quand elle Ã©tait mouillÃ©e, elle me collait un peu et me donnait assez de traction pour me lever et sortir. Je suis tombÃ© plusieurs fois en essayant de sortir, je me suis cognÃ© assez mal le bras. Je n'ai pas osÃ© prendre un bain aprÃ¨s Ã§a, juste quelques douches prudentes. J'en ai informÃ© le bureau, Ã©galement que je m'Ã©tais blessÃ©, et ils n'ont fait que demander le numÃ©ro de la chambre et dire que quelqu'un la regarderait. Ils ne l'ont jamais fait et n'ont exprimÃ© aucune inquiÃ©tude au sujet de ma blessure.
Il y a un magasin qui est ouvert Ã  23 heures. Mais c'Ã©tait surtout des trucs de Disney comme des tasses, des cadeaux junky, des croustilles et des bonbons, de l'eau et du coca. Pas de lait, de nourriture, de dentifrice, d'aspirine, de nourriture pour bÃ©bÃ© ... Vous devez vraiment apporter tout ce dont vous pourriez avoir besoin, car les chambres ne disposent que du shampoing et du savon standard, et il n'y a pas non plus de dÃ©panneur dans le village Disney.
(Avis d'origine)
I loved the Western theming! The western saddles as barstools are great! There's a fun kids play area that includes a Fort and Indian village. The rooms were nice, even my cheap standard room had plenty of space. Good breakfast buffet with a nice choice of foods. The western town layout with wagons and things is great. It is big though, several blocks. It's about a 15 minute walk to the parks. Lots of space for kids to run and play outside. There was a hairdryer and safe in the room. But no kettle, tea or coffee or microwave. A decent size TV, but not much to watch on it (not that anyone is going to be watching much TV at a Disney resort!). The WiFi in the room was okay, except one night there was no Internet connection. I had actually read that there was only WiFi in the hotel lobby and restaurant, so having it in the room was an unexpected surprise. Very clean, very safe with excellent security. All employees spoke both English and French, and some spoke other languages as well.
The cons of the place. It took FOREVER to check in. We stood in a queue for about a half hour, and that was on a slow day. They were taking nearly 10 minutes per family, and there was a lot of running back and forth by the employees. They didn't appear to have information they needed, or authority to do various things. There is no hot water, just lukewarm. Which made showers unpleasant and baths just cold. I did call maintenance, and a really pleasant guy came out, and managed to adjust something which warmed up the water to a tolerably comfortable temperature. The tubs are SUPER SLIPPERY(yeah all tubs are slippery, but this was ice slippery!), beware of this! I took a bath, and was unable to stand back up because my feet kept slipping from under me. There was a handle on one side, but I couldn't stand even holding on with two hands. I managed to get hold of the floor towel and get it into the tub, and when it got wet it stuck a bit and gave me enough traction to stand and get out. I fell several times trying to get out, bashed my arm pretty bad. I didn't dare take a bath after that, just some careful showers. I informed the desk of that, also that I'd hurt myself, and all they did was ask the room number and say someone would look at it. They never did, nor did they express any concern about my injury.
There is a shop that is open at 11pm. But it was mostly Disney stuff like mugs the junky gift items, potato chips and candy, and water and coke. No milk, food, toothpaste, aspirin, baby food... You really need to bring everything you might need with you, as the rooms only have the standard shampoo and soap, and there is no convenience store in the Disney village either.

Name: Joanne Cunningham
ReviewText:
We've stayed in 3 other hotels at Disneyland Paris, Sequoia Lodge, Hotel New York (soon to be Marvel hotel) and Newport Bay, and I can honestly say that this is my second favourite after Sequoia Lodge. Although it is considered one of the lower standard hotels (3* I think) it definitely hits the mark with theming and comfort. The rooms are decorated in a Toy Story style throughout, and the beds are so comfortable (may be a little hard for some but I like a firm bed). Rooms have air conditioning/thermostat heating, and are spacious enough. Couple of little niggles are that it is really hard to get the curtains closed in such a way to block any gaps, would easily be sorted by adding an extra two inches, and we didn't realise the flooring was laminate/wood effect- not great on the feet after hours of walking around the parks so I would recommend taking slippers! The bath is lovely and deep and great for a soak for those tired feet-i wish I had also taken some Epsom salts! There is a free shuttle to the parks but tbh the walk along the river takes 20 minutes tops for my little 5ft stature! And the queues to get in to the parks from the bus station are a good deal longer than those of people from the hotels. All in all a great hotel, and we would definitely stay there again (unless we're at Sequoia!)

My staying in the hotel was nice and pleasant .
I stayed in the Geronimo block for five days. The block is one of most distant part from the hotel but the silence and the area paid for the distance.
My room was really nice and always clean. The only problem I had was trying to have a hot shower, even when I came back earlier from the park, the water was warm to cold.
The breakfast was excellent everyday. The place was squeaky clean, the staff extremely helpful and there was a good variety of food.
The time waiting for the shuttle to the park was always around 10-12 and it would take around 3 minutes to the park itself. Excellent time to enjoy the Extra Magic Time.
Overall I can say that my staying was worth it and I would return to the same hotel but only trying to stay a little closer to the main entrance because in the morning the walk was basically a warm up to the long marathon in the park but in the evening/night after the park I was basically dragging myself to the hotel room through this long way.

The rooms are fine for what are advertised. The hallways are filthy, but again it's not the end of the world.
The staff is 95% useless. When we checked in they were slow and unfriendly as if us having the audacity to check in was an inconvienence for them.
Further when I booked my tickets I called the desk and they said they could print for me. So I walked the nearly 15 minutes from the outpost they put us in back to reception, waited in line again, and THEN they tell me that I need to send the PDF file to their email.
So I walked backed to the room (another 15 mins) to send the PDF.
Then I had to walk back to reception (another 15 mins) to get print out. (only a short wait)
Then I had to walk back to the room. (another 15 mins.)
I wasted an hour going back an forth, when if she would have simply told me the PDF email to begin with I could have picked it up on the way back from dinner.
The the air conditioning is a joke. And it is about 90F/32C. It's #(^*%&^#$% HOT outside!!!!
THe first night was very hard to sleep. It has to be about 25C/77F in the room. I turned down to the lowest setting at 17C, but there was NEVER any difference in the room temperature. Sleeping while you are hot and sticky is a nightmare. BOOOOOOOOO DISNEY!!!!!!!!!!!!!
After a half a day at the park I came back and called to ask them to come and look at the air conditioning to fix or otherwise improve.
They promised they would send someone. (no one came.)
After 40 minutes I called back. They promised 5 minutes.
Nobody came.
After 70 mintutes I called back. They put me on hold saying just 1 minute.
They never came back. They just kept picking up the phone and reengaging the hold button. They did this every min or so. I can only assume they are measured on extended hold times or that the phone starts making a reminder tone after a certain time so they pickup without talking and then just put me on hold again.
After about 20 minutes of this same non-sense I get transferred to housekeeping and she knew nothing about any of it. She said hold please and transferred me somewhere else that never answered.
So then I pressed the MANAGER button on the phone because this is crazy...
The phone just rings. Nobody answers. So i just let it ring. I figured if someone is there I can at least let them know I am as determined to talk to them as they are determined NOT to talk to me.
Finally after about 20 minutes of ringing someone picked up and I started to talk through my recent efforts, she was pleasant, but mostly trying to rush me off the phone. She asked me to hold and transferred me to the Reception manager.
I tried to explain, she cut me off to say she already knows and she's sorry and if I can wait another 30-60 minutes .
I have no hope that it will ever be resolved. My only hope is to tell you that staying here was a huge mistake. Not because of the hotel itself. It's adequate, although a bit dirty. It's a walk to Disney, but tolerable. But the people here don't seem to care one bit about the guests.
Somehow the normal Disney brand that I have become accustomed to around the rest of the world has failed to take shape here.
(The Disney park staff seems much nicer and more competent, so perhaps it is just the hotels problem.)
